The ten city-kingdoms of Cyprus are listed in a 673â€“672 BC inscription attributed to Esarhaddon, who ruled the Neo-Assyrian Empire from 681 BC to 669 BC. These kingdoms were Greek, Greco-Phoenician, and Greco-Eteocypriot in origin.
